&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Stripe is growing quickly and along with that, so are its operational requirements. Stripe Delivery Centers (SDC) are a brand new initiative to accelerate and expand Stripe’s operational capabilities via the creation of centralized hubs or centers of operational excellence. SDC will be staffed with Stripes, not vendors - we want Stripes at SDC to have the same level of tools and systems access as Stripes in other locations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is investing in building out its Creative Design team within SDC to reach users across the globe. The team designs comprehensive ad campaigns tailored for various platforms, ensuring that every visual element aligns with our marketing goals and engages our audience effectively. We create net-new creative content,&amp;nbsp; localize and adapt our content to meet the unique cultural and linguistic needs of different regions, to effectively present our message in global languages.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In addition to our work in advertising and web content, we also produce high-quality designs for presentations and other collateral aimed at large users and executive audiences. Our designs enhance the clarity and impact of our messages, making complex information accessible and engaging. Whether it&#39;s a pitch to clients or a strategy meeting with executives, we provide visually compelling designs that communicate our ideas confidently and effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Designers’ at Stripe’s SDC demonstrate a passion for captivating storytelling and great design. They use design systems to help tell compelling stories to a variety of audiences, and are well-versed at expanding, evolving, defining, and documenting flexible design systems and experiences that achieve bar-raising quality and consistency for the brand at scale. They are user-focused, have a strong understanding of the business, and are empathetic and inspiring. The ideal candidate excels across a variety of styles, crisply articulates design decisions, iterates quickly, and collaborates seamlessly with marketers, product managers, leaders, other designers, and other partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ideate, design, and produce world-class design solutions (static and motion) for a variety of events and deliverables including and not limited to presentations, posters, art, branding, and signage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can steward designers through large-scale design projects, providing art direction and ongoing guidance on creative strategy, execution, and localization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work across a wide variety of mediums (physical, digital, and everything in between) to create immersive storytelling and creative content that brings Stripe’s brand and product stories to life.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring design concepts to life through storyboarding, comps, and creative presentations, iterating on creative based on stakeholder feedback and internal testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with copywriters, static and motion designers, marketers, and ad operations to create interesting, visionary concepts that engage a global audience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor designers in design best practices and ideation, fostering an environment where everyone learns and grows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present ideas in a clear and focused way that builds consensus within the team and with stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive in identifying and implementing process optimization initiatives through automation and AI integration to enhance design quality and&amp;nbsp; efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6 to 10 years of relevant design and art direction experience, specifically for technical and product-driven companies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong track record of independently delivering work as well as influencing the work of other designers and internal teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Figma, Canva, and the Adobe Creative Cloud suite (for both motion and statics).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage a team of 3-4 Creative designers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to express and communicate a brand through distinct graphics, patterns, motion, interaction, and experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A hands-on maker with the skills to effectively communicate concepts, direction, and decisions to the team and external partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to find a meaningful balance between optimizing for speed and quality, while consistently delivering challenging, interesting, and pixel-perfect work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Persuasive and humble in explaining work, process, and decisions, with a craving for feedback to help design at your best.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work flexible hours, including late evenings in India, to facilitate real-time collaboration with global stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly detail-oriented, with a drive for perfection down to the last pixel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A multidisciplinary creative with a wide skill set who is comfortable working across different mediums and crafts, and is excited about experimenting with new technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior people management experience, with a track record of hiring, managing, and developing design talent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced at facilitating stakeholders to advance projects and advocate for design quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a cross-functional team at Stripe that operates at the intersection of real estate, design, and brand. We are a lean group focused on the end-to-end execution of high-touch physical environments. Our team acts as the bridge between creative vision and technical delivery, ensuring that Stripe’s physical footprint is built to an exacting standard of craft and operational excellence.&amp;nbsp; We are looking for builders who are energized by ambiguity and enjoy the process of turning a high-level concept into a tangible, functioning space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an Assistant Project Manager to be the operational backbone of a physical build-out. This is a &quot;jack-of-all-trades&quot; role for someone who is equally comfortable on a construction site as they are in a spreadsheet. You will support the end-to-end execution of a project, ensuring that the &quot;drumbeat&quot; of the work stays on track and that no detail is overlooked.&amp;nbsp; At Stripe, we are obsessively user-first. We believe that every touchpoint—including our physical environments—should reflect a commitment to craft, quality, and seamless experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Stripe, we prioritize a seamless onboarding experience. Your first four weeks are designed as an introductory period for mutual evaluation—ensuring the role, team, and pace align with your career goals and our high-performance standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive momentum:&lt;/strong&gt; Attend all workstream calls and own the action items. We use AI for raw notes, but you are responsible for coordinating stakeholders (internal and external) to ensure nothing stalls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive workstreams&lt;/strong&gt;: Manage execution in partnership with the lead, from kickoff through completion—everything from sourcing vendor options and securing budget approvals to collaborating with internal teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Be on-site&lt;/strong&gt;: Be on-site as needed to verify that our standards of craft and delivery are being met across all physical touchpoints.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support team scaling&lt;/strong&gt;: Manage the logistics of expanding project capacity, including vendor sourcing, partner onboarding, leveraging AI tools, and contractor coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Draft weekly updates&lt;/strong&gt;: Turn complex updates from across the project into clear, dense weekly notes for leadership. You possess the ability to turn project noise into actionable signal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a highly organized, collaborative partner who thrives in fast-moving, ambiguous environments and makes the people around you more effective. You love creating thoughtful experiences and environments, with a commitment to high-touch, on-brand execution. You have a track record of taking broad goals, building a clear path forward, and keeping priorities, details, and communication moving with minimal friction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Real estate experience: &lt;/strong&gt;You have 3–5 years of experience in real estate operations, owner’s representation, or hospitality development. You are a &quot;high-agency&quot; operator who loves the &quot;how&quot; of making things happen.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Users’first mindset:&lt;/strong&gt; At Stripe, we are obsessively user-first. You likely come from a background where the guest or customer experience is paramount—such as consumer-facing retail or premium hospitality. You understand that the quality of a space directly impacts the person using it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A &quot;force multiplier&quot; mentality:&lt;/strong&gt; You are a super team player who thrives in a close-knit, collaborative environment and makes everyone around you more effective.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;High agency track record: &lt;/strong&gt;You have 3–5 years of experience in roles that require exceptional organization and the ability to navigate ambiguity. Your former colleagues describe you as the person who &quot;just gets it done.&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strong communication:&lt;/strong&gt; You never let an action item drop and can distill complex updates into clear, actionable briefings for leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial and administrative rigor: &lt;/strong&gt;You have experience managing project budgets, navigating procurement workflows, and maintaining meticulous financial records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical leverage:&lt;/strong&gt; You are proficient at using AI and modern productivity tools to automate routine tasks and accelerate project delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an experienced regulatory licensing professional to manage our Audit &amp;amp; Regulatory Affairs team. In this role, you will coordinate with Stripe’s Legal, Financial Crimes, Finance, Accounting, Product, and Security teams, to (i) coordinate and submit regulatory license applications; (ii) manage license renewals and licence maintenance items; (iii) manage US regulatory exams and inquiries; and (iv) oversee other aspects of the team’s day-to-day activities, with a focus on licensing and exam activities related to digital assets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe’s mission is to increase the GDP of the internet. We build the most powerful and flexible tools for running an internet business. We handle billions of dollars each year and enable millions of users around the world to scale faster and more efficiently by building their businesses on Stripe. More than 80% of American adults bought something through Stripe in the last year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Namely, Stripe’s North America regulatory affairs program plays a critical role in ensuring Stripe effectively manages its regulatory requirements and ongoing regulatory obligations for certain licensed US and Canadian entities. The role provides an excellent opportunity for a talented candidate to deploy their cross-functional licensing and regulatory exam management skills in a fast-paced and rigorous environment, enhance their regulatory risk management expertise, learn about digital assets, carve out opportunities to grow and develop, as well as lead a team of skilled and talented professionals. The successful candidate will gain wide ranging exposure to Stripe&#39;s diverse range of business lines, senior leadership, and the governance and workings of the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will be a self-starter who is exceptionally organized, thorough and detail-oriented, with a background in financial services, payments, digital assets, or other regulated sectors. In this role, you will get a chance to help build, enhance, mature and evolve our regulatory licensing and exam programs and be a key cross-functional partner. Stripe is both a technology company and a financial services company, and you will need to be comfortable in both worlds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Audit &amp;amp; Regulatory Management Lead will help to ensure that all of the relevant components of the regulatory affairs program for licensed US and Canadian entities remain current and compliant, oversee managing and executing US regulatory examinations, and support our Compliance Audit Strategy, with the expectation to build a team who, in due time, will manage and drive exam oversight globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate responses to state regulatory inquiries, filings, forms, applications, renewals, surety bonds, and anything else required for license maintenance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in managing regulatory exams and inquiries, responding to regularly exam matters and monitoring the implementation and closure of any remediation items&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay abreast of regulatory changes, particularly with respect to digital assets, and how they impact regulatory affairs’ licensing and exam management program activities and responsibilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain relationships with internal and external partners and business units, relevant state and local agencies, licensing consultants, and outside counsel&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work proactively with Legal, Finance, Financial Crimes, Affiliate Officers, Product, and other key stakeholders on managing the regulatory affairs’s licensing and examination program&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support any end-to-end licensing, examination and related ad hoc inquiries as required in partnership with key stakeholders&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage in special projects in support of the regulatory affairs program in North America&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Political Science, Economics, or a related field&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years experience in financial services, with significant experience in payments— familiarity with money transmitter statutes, NMLS, the BSA, and other areas of financial services, such as digital assets, lending, loan brokering and collections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A history of professional achievement, including excellent academic credentials and success at a payments startup, financial institution, public sector organization, law enforcement agency, or top in-house legal department&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated familiarity with leveraging Generative AI and agentic workflows to automate preparing responses to routine questions and requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to effectively and credibly communicate with senior executives, regulators and other stakeholders&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great interpersonal and critical thinking skills, good judgment, and the ability to work effectively with a wide variety of people inside and outside the company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Robust communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

