&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Agent Experience&lt;/strong&gt; team is at the forefront of a monumental shift in how the world interacts with financial infrastructure. Our mission is to make Stripe as seamless and powerful for AI agent users as it is for human users. We’re building the infrastructure you need to turn AI agents into active economic participants, making it simple for your autonomous systems to transact, scale, and thrive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a high-growth, rapidly evolving space. We operate with the speed and creative autonomy of a startup, backed by the scale and rigor of Stripe. You will lead a talented group of engineers navigating the rapidly evolving Agentic AI landscape, building the tools and systems that will define how AI interacts with the global economy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Engineering Manager for Agent Experience, you will be responsible for scaling a mission-critical team from its early stages. You will balance deep technical strategy in the AI space with a relentless bias-for-action, ensuring we ship high-leverage tools for developers and their agents.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead and Scale:&lt;/strong&gt; Build and manage a high-performing team of 10+ engineers, ranging from early-career to Staff level. You will own the hiring roadmap and the professional development of your team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Define Agentic Strategy:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with product and executive leadership to shape the long-term vision of how AI agents consume Stripe’s APIs and services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Execute with Urgency:&lt;/strong&gt; Foster a &quot;bias-for-action&quot; culture that allows the team to ship rapidly in an evolving market without sacrificing the reliability expected of financial infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Technical Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt; Oversee the design and delivery of complex back-end systems and developer tools, ensuring they are extensible, secure, and intuitive for both humans and agents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate Cross-Functionally:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as a primary bridge between your team and Stripe’s senior leadership, influencing company-wide strategy for AI integration and agentic workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Navigate High-Stakes Environments:&lt;/strong&gt; Ensure all innovations meet Stripe&#39;s high bar for security and compliance, particularly as we operate within regulated financial ecosystems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5+ years of engineering management experience&lt;/strong&gt;, with a proven track record of managing and growing teams of 10+ engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deep domain expertise&lt;/strong&gt; in the Agentic AI space or a strong background in building sophisticated developer tools and back-end systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exceptional communication skills&lt;/strong&gt;, with the ability to distill complex technical concepts into clear strategic frameworks for peers and executives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience in rapid-growth environments&lt;/strong&gt;, specifically a history of successful, high-volume hiring and team scaling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical proficiency&lt;/strong&gt; to engage deeply with Staff-level engineers on system architecture, API design, and AI model integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A &quot;dual-track&quot; career history with experience in both early-stage startups and high-growth, at-scale technology companies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience navigating high-stakes, regulated industries such as Fintech or Healthcare.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong point of view on the future of AI-driven economies and the &quot;agentic&quot; evolution of software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Agentic payments is a team that’s building news API and integration experiences for agentic commerce online. We think that the proliferation of consumer-facing AI experiences will unlock new ways that consumers buy things online, and our existing payments experiences need to evolve to new commercial models that cutting-edge builders are starting. Our first launch, Instant Checkout in collaboration with OpenAI, took the industry by storm and we’re bringing experiences like that to the entire universe of AI agents, and sellers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Engineering Manager on Agentic Commerce, you’ll own the shaping and delivery of transformative products that redefine how commerce works, making it more fluid, automated, and aligned with user intent. You’ll collaborate closely with product management, design, data science, and marketing to unlock new opportunities for our customers and partners globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our north star provides a new integration shape for AI agents who are looking to build agent-powered online commerce experiences, via their Stripe integration. They will have access to our entire suite of connected sellers, and can focus on the experience with the end-user. Enabling an AI agent to do this requires new API primitives, new dashboard surfaces, and deep thought about what financial and e-commerce complexity Stripe can simplify on their behalf.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build full stack solutions across Stripe&#39;s ecosystem, including back end services, dashboard interfaces, money movement systems, and integrations with other Stripe primitives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner deeply with product management and design to ship high impact features that increase user autonomy and reduce friction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills: comfort diving into data to test hypotheses and make informed trade-offs. Comfortable setting success metrics for the team to ensure that our solutions are enterprise grade out of the box and can meet Stripe’s reliability SLOs quickly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally across Stripe’s broader platform and product teams to integrate agentic commerce capabilities seamlessly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage directly with users (particularly large enterprises) to understand their business needs and translate requirements into novel product shapes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of engineering experience with a computer science background with hands on development expertise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience coaching and developing senior and staff level individual contributors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience of leading initiatives that touch large engineering organizations, spanning multiple teams to influence tech roadmap planning and execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills, structuring ambiguous concepts clearly and from first principles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thrive in a collaborative environment involving different functions, stakeholders, and subject matter experts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep empathy for users balancing autonomy and guidance in digital commerce experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of engineering management experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building APIs or new integration experiences for users, several of them being enterprise grade&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ve been on the found team of a business / startup, taking a product from 0-1&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in eCommerce&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI-native and very comfortable autonomously solving problems with agentic AI tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The APAC &amp;amp; EMEA Cards team powers the processing of hundreds of billions of dollars in card payments annually, enabling users to accept card payments from Asia Pacific, Europe, and Middle East regions. As the Engineering Manager for the team, you’ll have responsibility for expanding the reach of Stripe’s global payments network, delivering the best-in-class experience for card payments in these regions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you’ll be making some of the most significant strategic, product, and technical decisions for card payments at Stripe. The systems this team builds enables our users to create a single integration with Stripe, then take payments across an ever-expanding set of card networks and grow their businesses globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with other Stripe leaders to author Stripe’s card payments strategy in APAC &amp;amp; EMEA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop engineers on the team, helping them advance in their careers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Empower the engineering team to achieve a high level of technical productivity, reliability and simplicity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage processes to help the team do its best work and interface effectively with the rest of Stripe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to engineering-wide initiatives as a member of Stripe’s engineering management team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recruit great engineers, in collaboration with Stripe’s recruiting team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may be a fit for this role if:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You thrive on a high level of autonomy and responsibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You encourage a healthy work environment that’s both supportive and challenging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re excited to help engineers develop new skills and advance in their careers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re clear and persuasive in writing and in person&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You lead by example, by setting the right context, and by helping teammates do their best work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re technical enough to ask engineers good questions about architecture and product decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS or MS in Computer Science or equivalent technical field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of Engineering Management experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in a Software Engineering role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to define and drive complex initiatives/projects&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience hiring top talent, building diverse, high-performing teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to communicate both with technical and non-technical audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with payments-related products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working in global and cross-regional environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using AI tools to improve team execution, quality, and overall effectiveness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies - from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups - use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Connect is Stripe&#39;s leading product for marketplaces, on-demand services, e-commerce site builders, invoicing platforms, professional SaaS products, fundraising platforms, rental management platforms, and more. By utilizing the power of Connect, users in each of these categories can link multiple parties for the exchange of goods or services. These users rely on Connect for the crucial function of reliably routing payments between these parties.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;By powering fast, flexible, compliant, and cost-efficient routing of payments on the internet, Connect not only spurs the creation of innovative business models, but it also enables organizations (whether they are businesses, nonprofits, or governmental agencies) to channel previously-offline payments to the internet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This team delivers the primary dashboard experience for Connect platforms - the surface through which platforms understand, manage, and grow their business on Stripe. The work spans analytics and insights, platform onboarding, connected account management, and the systems that enable other Stripe teams to build high-quality experiences for platform users. You&#39;ll lead a distributed full-stack engineering team working across APIs, frontend surfaces, and data pipelines that directly impact platform satisfaction and retention.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Engineering Manager at Stripe, you will play a pivotal role in driving the success of your team and the broader organization. Your responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading engineering and design processes, coaching, mentoring, and supporting your team as they build innovative solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with stakeholders across product, design, infrastructure, marketing, and operations to ensure alignment on projects and objectives and shaping the team’s strategy and roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Owning problems from end-to-end by managing diverse systems, processes, and technologies, while continuously seeking opportunities to optimize efficiency and user experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Upholding high engineering standards, ensuring consistency across codebases, and implementing best practices throughout your team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recruiting top engineering talent in partnership with Stripe’s recruiting team to build a diverse and high-performing team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting your team members&#39; career growth by providing insights and development opportunities tailored to their goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of engineering management experience, directly managing and growing teams of 5+ engineers focused on building and shipping products at scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of full time software development experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building extensible, leveraged software solutions that scale to different kinds of user needs, with the ability to empathize with users and advocate for exceptional user experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving skills, with a history of creatively tackling complex challenges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in dealing with ambiguity and executing on multiple high-impact work streams simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to fostering a supportive, feedback-driven, and challenging work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical proficiency to engage thoughtfully with engineers about architecture and product design, offering valuable insights when necessary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A mindset of autonomy and entrepreneurship, where you&#39;re excited to take responsibility and drive initiatives forward&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a strong product and design sense, and enjoy finding elegant solutions to complex problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience thriving in cross-functional environments, demonstrating rigorous thinking, effective decision-making, and ability to build strong cross-team relationships&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience building and leading a distributed team that works across multiple locations and time zones&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies-from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups-use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We build and operate Stripe’s Event Infrastructure — the reliable, low-latency backbone that captures, routes, and persists billions of events daily. We design resilient, scalable systems for real-time ingestion, filtering, transformation, and high-throughput delivery to downstream consumers. We prioritize observability, backpressure control, and graceful degradation to keep payments and platform features running under any load. By automating operations and iterating on capacity and cost optimizations, we enable product teams to build on a predictable event-streaming foundation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Impact You’ll Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Engineering Manager in the infrastructure organization, you are expected to see problems others don&#39;t and rally people to independently create solutions. You will move beyond day-to-day management to act as an industry leader, effectively advocating for your organization&#39;s mission, values, and impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architect the Org &amp;amp; Culture:&lt;/strong&gt; Design and scale a high-leverage org structure. You will define what &quot;Elite Engineering&quot; looks like, setting the bar for craftsmanship and operational rigor serving as a blueprint for Stripe infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vision and Strategy:&lt;/strong&gt; Define the scope, vision, and goals for your organization with little or no guidance from your manager. You will anticipate industry trends and use them to influence Stripe&#39;s long-range plans, setting direction on a multi-year timeframe for Stripe’s online storage layer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Operational Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt; You will instill a culture of rigorous thinking and meticulous craftsmanship, ensuring our infrastructure remains proactive and resilient as Stripe’s business demands evolve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bridge Engineering &amp;amp; Business:&lt;/strong&gt; You will collaborate with cross-functional leaders to align deep engineering needs with global business growth forecasts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build the Future Team:&lt;/strong&gt; Proactively invest in the development of the organization and its people at all levels. You will obsess over talent, hiring and coaching other managers to elevate the skills of the leadership team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a visionary leader who thrives on operating Tier0 infrastructure and building world-class teams. You should be equally comfortable in high-level strategic conversations and deep-diving into database internals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proven Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Minimum 5 years of experience in a technical engineering management role; overseeing strategic projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Systems Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt; A deep technical background in distributed systems and experience operating Tier0 infrastructure at massive scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Mindset:&lt;/strong&gt; Ability to bridge deep engineering needs with global business growth forecasts and product strategy, specifically building abstractions that empower thousands of other developers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Navigator:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience managing through ambiguity and making critical trade-offs between reliability, efficiency, and long-term architectural health.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Curiosity and Humility&lt;/strong&gt;: A deep curiosity about the &quot;nuts-and-bolts&quot; of the business (e.g., global money movement) combined with the humility to continue learning and growing as a leader&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; Exceptional written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scale and Infrastructure: &lt;/strong&gt;Successfully shipped and operated critical infrastructure (database internals or related field) with significant responsibility over funds and/or critical data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Ambiguity:&lt;/strong&gt; Ability to navigate complex, high-impact work where you must define your own scope and vision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Influence: &lt;/strong&gt;A track record of getting other teams on board with your vision to support execution in a way that benefits the broader company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In-office expectations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In-Office:&lt;/strong&gt; Stripe is a &quot;Live&quot; culture. You will be expected to spend at least 50% of your time in your local hub to foster high-bandwidth, in-person collaboration.&lt;/p&gt;

