&lt;li&gt;Prior experience in a sales and/or customer-facing role at a high growth technology company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Sales Manager, Commercial (Existing Business), you will play a critical role in driving Stripe’s growth by leading the strategy, execution, and optimization of our go-to-market efforts with existing Mid Market customers. In this role, you will focus on deepening relationships, expanding product adoption, and maximizing customer value across Stripe’s growing Mid Market base. You will lead a team of high-performing Account Executives, supporting their development while also engaging directly with strategic accounts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a proactive and customer-obsessed leader who thrives in a high-growth, ambiguous environment. You’ve successfully managed and scaled high-performing teams and know how to drive impact by balancing strategy, execution, and hands-on leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, coach, and grow a team of Account Executives focused on driving revenue growth from Stripe’s existing Mid Market customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own performance against key growth and retention metrics, including expansion, cross-sell, and renewal targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with senior leadership to refine the long-term strategy for Stripe’s existing business sales motion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Account Executives in developing consultative, solution-oriented approaches to expand customer adoption of Stripe’s products and services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a high-performance, inclusive team culture that emphasizes learning, ownership, and measurable impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with Product, Marketing, Customer Success, and other teams to improve customer experience and retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personally engage with key accounts, including executive-level stakeholders, to build lasting partnerships and drive long-term value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advocate for the needs and feedback of existing customers to inform Stripe’s product roadmap and strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Who You Are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum qualifications listed below. If you meet these, we encourage you to apply — preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum Requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of relevant sales experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience leading a team of quota-carrying sales professionals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of driving revenue growth through expansion and retention within an existing customer base.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to hire, develop, and manage high-performing sales teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong executive presence and ability to build and maintain relationships with senior customer stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort working with technical products and the ability to translate complex concepts into business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role requires working from the Chicago office three (3) days per week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in a growth-stage internet or software company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of managing complex sales cycles and driving multi-product adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing teams in offices outside of company headquarters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with payments or fintech industry and related customer needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Stripe’s Commercial team sits within Stripe’s Americas Sales organization and is responsible for acquisition, expansion, and growth of mid market accounts in North America. This team sells the entire suite of Stripe products and owns the full customer lifecycle. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;As a Sales Manager, Commercial (New Business), you will play an instrumental role in fueling Stripe’s growth through defining the sales motion and GTM processes needed to acquire, grow and expand mid market accounts. In this role, you will build the foundation of a new team and GTM motion at Stripe. You will hire and lead a team of high-performing Account Executives, helping them to develop their skills and deliver on their ambitious targets, as well as roll your sleeves up to work directly with customers. We are looking for a proactive leader who has demonstrated success dealing with ambiguity, operating in a high-growth environment, managing high-performing teams and solving complicated problems with limited oversight. Ideal candidates will have management and leadership experience scaling a technology sales team and possess first-class analytical, communication and relationship-building skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Recruit, develop and lead a team of Account Executives who focus on mid market businesses&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Work with senior leadership to develop the long-term vision and strategy for the team, and manage day-to-day operations with a focus on performance against key sales and growth metrics&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Be accountable for increasing revenue and new client acquisition at high rates of growth&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Coach and guide the team in developing consultative and solution-based sales skills&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Inspire, motivate and enable development of team members to promote career growth and impact for Stripe&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Work collaboratively and cross-functionally across the organization to implement programs that drive overall efficiency for the team&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Deeply understand the needs of mid market customers to shape Stripe’s products and solutions to meet their needs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Play a personal and direct role in building and maintaining enduring customer relationships, up to C-level.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
